			elseif AntiLock.Mode == "Down" then

				Hrp.Velocity = Vel

				RunService.RenderStepped:Wait()
				Hrp.Velocity = Vel

				Hrp.Velocity = Vel * -1
				RunService.RenderStepped:Wait()
				Hrp.Velocity = Vel

				Hrp.Velocity = Hrp.CFrame.lookVector * AntiLock.LookVecAmt

				Hrp.Velocity = Vel

				RunService.RenderStepped:Wait()
				Hrp.Velocity = Vel

				Hrp.AssemblyLinearVelocity = AntiLock.DesyncVel
				Hrp.CFrame = Hrp.CFrame * CFrame.Angles(0, math.rad(AntiLock.DesyncAngles), 0)

				Hrp.AssemblyLinearVelocity = AlVel

title: Emacs config tangling bootstrapper
content:
#+PROPERTY: header-args:emacs-lisp :tangle ./tangled.el

Welcome to tangling elisp out of org files! I swear it's easier than it sounds.

Save this as an org file in your .emacs.d directory, put point in the first block, and use =C-c C-c= to evaluate it.

Then you can put your entire init.el in the second code block, and saving this file should create a new file, =tangled.el= with the provided code and your current config. Now break your config up into blocks and sort them with org headlines and text descriptions!

Make sure you test that the generated file can be evaluated (=M-x eval-buffer=) and then change the output target in the PROPERTY line at the top to be =./init.el=.

#+begin_src emacs-lisp

  (org-babel-do-load-languages
   'org-babel-load-languages '((emacs-lisp . t))) ;; have babel highlight elisp

  (setq org-confirm-babel-evaluate nil)           ;; C-c C-c to evaluate code blocks without requesting confirmation

  ;; string expander for code blocks
  (require 'org-tempo)

  ;; Type <el TAB to automatically insert an elisp code block
  ;; it will look like "#+begin_src emacs-lisp" and "#+end_src"
  (add-to-list 'org-structure-template-alist '("el" . "src emacs-lisp"))

  (defun my/org-babel-tangle-config ()
  "When saving the org file, automatically tangle it into an elisp file without prompting for confirmation."
    (when (string-equal (buffer-file-name)
                        (expand-file-name "~/.emacs.d/config.org")) ; Change this to be whatever you name your org file
      (let ((org-confirm-babel-evaluate nil))
        (org-babel-tangle))))

  (add-hook 'org-mode-hook (lambda () (add-hook 'after-save-hook #'my/org-babel-tangle-config)))

#+end_src

You can put your current configuration in here:

#+begin_src emacs-lisp

  ;; Right here!

#+end_src

from tkinter import Frame, Label, Tk, CENTER, LEFT, RIGHT, Entry, Button
from tkinter import ttk

class TravelReport:
    def __init__(self):
        self.window = Tk()
        self.window.title('Пътен лист 2023г.')
        self.window.geometry('1200x840+200+10')
        self.window.resizable(True, False)
        self.window.attributes('-topmost', 'true')

        self.widgets = {}

        self.first_data_line_row = 0
        self.data_lines_count = 0

        self.frame_1 = self.get_frame(place_on=self.window)
        self.create_travel_rep()
        add_row = Button(self.window, text="Нов ред", width=8, command=self.add_row)
        add_row.grid(row=0, column=1)

        del_row = Button(self.window, text="Изтрий", width=8, command=self.del_last_row)
        del_row.grid(row=1, column=1)


        self.window.mainloop()

    def get_label(self, place_on, row_x, col_y, span_row=1, span_col=1, height=1, text='', anc=CENTER):
        label = Label(place_on, text=text, font=('Times New Roman', 10, 'bold'), bg='white', height=height,
                    anchor=anc, fg='black', justify='center', )
        label.grid(row=row_x, column=col_y, padx=(1, 1), pady=(1, 1), sticky='nswe', rowspan=span_row, columnspan=span_col)
        return label

    # -----------------FRAMES------------------------------------------------
    def get_frame(self, place_on, ):
        frame = Frame(place_on,  width=100, height=100)
        frame.grid(row=0, column=0)
        return frame

    # -----------------ENTRIES------------------------------------------------
    def get_entry(self, place_on, r, c,  j=LEFT, name=None, space_x=(1, 1) ):

        entry = Entry(place_on, bd=2, name=name, justify=j, relief="flat")
        # entry.place(x=x, y=y)

        pass

    def create_travel_rep(self):
        frame_1 = self.frame_1

        self.get_label(place_on=frame_1, row_x=1, col_y=0, text="БЕНЗИН", height=1)
        # get_list_box или combo_box за избор на месеца
        self.get_label(place_on=frame_1, row_x=1, col_y=3, height=1, text="Януари",)
        self.get_label(place_on=frame_1, row_x=0, col_y=6, height=1, text="обем: ")

        self.get_label(place_on=frame_1, row_x=2, col_y=6, height=1, text="Наличност:")
        self.get_label(place_on=frame_1, row_x=2, col_y=7, height=1, text="52,25")

        self.get_label(place_on=frame_1, row_x=33, col_y=7, text="135,66")

        self.get_label(place_on=frame_1, row_x=34, col_y=4, text="250")

        self.get_label(place_on=frame_1, row_x=34, col_y=7, text="450,51")

        self.get_label(place_on=frame_1, row_x=35, col_y=6, text="Остатък (л):")
        self.get_label(place_on=frame_1, row_x=35, col_y=7, text="53,33")

    def add_row(self):
        if self.data_lines_count > 20:
            return
        self.data_lines_count += 1
        new_data_line_row = self.first_data_line_row + self.data_lines_count
        self.create_row(self.frame_1, new_data_line_row)

    def del_last_row(self):
        if self.data_lines_count < 3:
            return
        last_data_line_row = self.first_data_line_row + self.data_lines_count
        for col in range(7+1):
            widgets = self.frame_1.grid_slaves(last_data_line_row, col)
            for widget in widgets:
                widget.grid_remove()
                del(widget)

        self.data_lines_count -= 1

#!/usr/bin/env python3

###############################################################################
# SOURCE: https://tarkov-time.adam.id.au/
# SOURCE: https://www.reddit.com/r/EscapefromTarkov/comments/u89ccn/i_made_a_physical_eft_clock_so_i_can_tell_when/i5kg22h/
#
#  # pip install -U arrow
#  import arrow
#
#  def eft_time(rightTime=False):
#      offset = convertHoursToSeconds(3) # St. Petersburg - MSK (UTC + 3)
#
#      if rightTime:
#          offset += convertHoursToSeconds(12)
#
#      tarkovTime = arrow.get(arrow.utcnow().timestamp() * tarkovTimeScalar + offset)
#      return tarkovTime.format("HH:mm:ss")
#
###############################################################################

import datetime

def eft_time(rightTime=False):
    offset = convertHoursToSeconds(3) # St. Petersburg - MSK (UTC + 3)

    if rightTime:
        offset += convertHoursToSeconds(12)

    # utcnow = datetime.datetime.utcnow() # Returns wrong time. I think https://stackoverflow.com/a/24666683 is the reason.
    # utcnow = datetime.datetime.utcnow().replace(tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc) # Works.
    utcnow = datetime.datetime.now(datetime.timezone.utc) # Works.

    tarkovTime = datetime.datetime.utcfromtimestamp(utcnow.timestamp() * tarkovTimeScalar + offset)

    # SOURCE [incomplete and slightly off i think]: https://escapefromtarkov.fandom.com/wiki/How_to_Play_Guide_for_Escape_from_Tarkov#IRL_time_vs_EFT_time
    # Event     Time            Notes
    # Dawn      05:00           Light on the horizon.
    # Sunrise   05:45           Direct sunlight above the horizon.
    # Sunset    21:30
    # Night     21:50 - 22:15   Full darkness begins.
    # Moonrise  00:00

    # Totally morb, like midnight but morb.
    if tarkovTime.hour >= 21:
        event = 'PerfectDark'

    # Sun didn't set but its starting to get morb.
    elif tarkovTime.hour >= 20:
        event = 'Morbnoon'

    elif tarkovTime.hour >= 16:
        event = 'Afternoon'

    elif tarkovTime.hour >= 12:
        event = 'Highnoon'

    elif tarkovTime.hour >= 8:
        event = 'Morning'

    # Early morning, still dark.
    elif tarkovTime.hour >= 7:
        event = 'Morbing'

    # Sunrise and moonset and an opportunity for another meme.
    elif tarkovTime.hour >= 6:
        event = 'Twilight'

    # Moon at its highest position (approximately 45 degrees above the horizon).
    elif tarkovTime.hour >= 3:
        event = 'Highmoon'

    # Moon is rising, but still morb.
    else:
        event = 'Lowmoon'

    return '{} {}'.format(tarkovTime.strftime("%H:%M:%S"), event)

def eft_time_hour(rightTime=False):
    offset = convertHoursToSeconds(3) # St. Petersburg - MSK (UTC + 3)

    if rightTime:
        offset += convertHoursToSeconds(12)

    # utcnow = datetime.datetime.utcnow() # Returns wrong time. I think https://stackoverflow.com/a/24666683 is the reason.
    # utcnow = datetime.datetime.utcnow().replace(tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc) # Works.
    utcnow = datetime.datetime.now(datetime.timezone.utc) # Works.

    tarkovTime = datetime.datetime.utcfromtimestamp(utcnow.timestamp() * tarkovTimeScalar + offset)

    return int(tarkovTime.strftime("%H"))

# Tarkov time moves at seven seconds per second.
tarkovTimeScalar = 7

def convertHoursToSeconds(hours):
    return 3600 * hours

# SOURCE: https:#www.programiz.com/python-programming/time/sleep
import time
def sleep(milliseconds):
    time.sleep(milliseconds / 1000)

# SOURCE: https://www.delftstack.com/howto/python/python-clear-console/
import os
def cls():
    os.system('cls' if os.name in ('nt', 'dos') else 'clear')

# -----

# SOURCE: https://www.saic.it/bach-color-linux/

BLACK = '\033[30m'
RED = '\033[31m'
GREEN = '\033[32m'
YELLOW = '\033[33m'
BLUE = '\033[34m'
MAGENTA = '\033[35m'
CYAN = '\033[36m'
WHITE = '\033[37m'
UNDERLINE = '\033[4m'
RESET = '\033[0m'

def Color(var, color):
    return color + str(var) + RESET

# -----

NIGHT=RED
DAY=CYAN

while True:
    cls()
    # print(' [{}] [{}]'.format(eft_time(), eft_time(True)))
    # print()
    # print(' 03:00 Highmoon')
    # print(' 06:00 Twilight')
    # print(' 07:00 Morbing')
    # print(' 08:00 Morning')
    # print(' 12:00 Highnoon')
    # print(' 16:00 Afternoon')
    # print(' 20:00 Morbnoon')
    # print(' 21:00 PerfectDark')
    # print(' 24:00 Lowmoon')

    hour = eft_time_hour()
    print(Color(' [{}] '.format(eft_time()), DAY if hour >= 6 and hour < 20 else NIGHT), end='')

    hour = eft_time_hour(True)
    print(Color('[{}]'.format(eft_time(True)), DAY if hour >= 6 and hour < 20 else NIGHT))

    print()
    print(Color(' 03:00 Highmoon', NIGHT))
    print(Color(' 06:00 Twilight', DAY))
    print(Color(' 07:00 Morbing', DAY))
    print(Color(' 08:00 Morning', DAY))
    print(Color(' 12:00 Highnoon', DAY))
    print(Color(' 16:00 Afternoon', DAY))
    print(Color(' 20:00 Morbnoon', NIGHT))
    print(Color(' 21:00 PerfectDark', NIGHT))
    print(Color(' 24:00 Lowmoon', NIGHT))
    sleep(1000)

	else

			},

			[3] = game.Workspace,
			[4] = tonumber(Rate.Text)

		workspace:WaitForChild("ServerStuff"):WaitForChild("playAudio"):FireServer(unpack(args))

end

end)
local togga = true
UIS.InputBegan:Connect(function(i, gpe)
	if gpe then return end
	if killed == true then return end
	if i.KeyCode == Enum.KeyCode.U then
		if togga == false then
			savepos = Sound.Position
			Sound:TweenPosition(UDim2.new(-1.3, 0, savepos.Y.Scale, 0), Enum.EasingDirection.Out, Enum.EasingStyle.Quad, 0.7) 
		else

			else

			end

	if i.KeyCode == Enum.KeyCode.F3 then
		playsound()
	end

		game:GetService("StarterGui"):SetCore("SendNotification", {

			Icon = "rbxassetid://13813545954"
		})
	end

title: Filter signals (emails) on a stock chart for long/short position trades
content:
#!/usr/bin/env python
"""
This module uses a few filters or smoothers on a
stock chart to facilitate the potential generation of
long/short trading signals (for "position trades").
"""
# tsla_alerts_on_chart_signals.py
#
#
# faultcode, 2023-05-07/08/09/10/11/12/13/15/17/19
#
#
# manual start in Ubuntu: nohup python3 tsla_alerts_on_chart_signals.py &
#
# code analysis: 9.91/10 (2023-05-13)
#


import time
import datetime

import smtplib
from email.utils import formatdate

import yfinance
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas_ta as ta  # Pandas TA - A Technical Analysis Library in Python 3


DATA_FILE = "TSLA_alerts_on_signals_data.txt"  # current dir is working dir

# days for moving average:
MA2 = 45  # WMA
MA4 = 65  # John Ehlers’ Super Smoother

# stock and index symbols:
sym1 = yfinance.Ticker("TSLA")

NAME1 = "Tesla, Nasdaq [USD, daily open]"

G = .0500   # α
H = 0.0009  # β
DT = 1.0  # sample time
NAME19 = """α-β filtered: """ + f'α = {G:.4f}, ' + f'β = {H:.5f}'

NAME5 = "weighted moving average " + str(MA2) + "d"

SSF_POLES = 2
NAME17 = "Ehlers' Super Smoother filter: " + str(MA4) + "d" + ", poles=" + str(SSF_POLES)

CHART_TIMESPAN = 0.75
# years: a little bit more than one calendar year of quotes
# to allow filters to swing in

DAYS_STR = str(int(CHART_TIMESPAN * 365)) + "d"



############################################################
#
# α-β filter:
def a_b_filter(data):
    """
    Performs g-h filter on 1 state variable with a fixed g and h.
    'data' contains the data to be filtered.
    'x0' is the initial value for our state variable
    'dx' is the initial change rate for our state variable
    'g' is the g-h's g scale factor
    'h' is the g-h's h scale factor
    'dt' is the length of the time step
    """

    x_est = data[0]
    results = []
    dx_new = 0.0

    for meas in data:
        # prediction step
        x_pred = x_est + (dx_new * DT)
        dx_old = dx_new

        # update step
        residual = meas - x_pred
        dx_new = dx_old + H * (residual) / DT
        x_est = x_pred + G * residual
        results.append(x_est)

    return np.array(results)
#
############################################################



############################################################
#
def long_crossover(quotes, smoother):
    """
    check if a long crossover happened at open at smoother type
    """
    filt_diff = quotes - smoother
    filt_diff_val = filt_diff.values

    last_filt_diff = filt_diff_val[-1]

    # True if long crossover happened
    # False if long crossover did not happen
    return bool(last_filt_diff > 0.0)


def short_crossover(quotes, smoother):
    """
    check if a short crossover happened at open at smoother type
    """
    filt_diff = quotes - smoother
    filt_diff_val = filt_diff.values

    last_filt_diff = filt_diff_val[-1]

    # True if long crossover happened
    # False if long crossover did not happen
    return bool(last_filt_diff < 0.0)
#
############################################################



############################################################
#
def hardcopy():
    """
    plot stock chart with open quotes and filters/smoothers on open
    """
    first_date = str(sym1_hist.index[0].date())
    last_date  = str(sym1_hist.index[-1].date())
    suptitle = first_date + ' - ' + last_date

    x_1 = sym1_hist.index  # DatetimeIndex

    fig = plt.figure(figsize=(16, 9))

    a_x = plt.subplot(111)
    a_x.plot(x_1, sym1_hist['Open'], label=NAME1, color='tab:blue')
    a_x.plot(x_1, sym1_hist['Open'], 'bo', markersize=4)

    a_x.plot(x_1, sym1_hist['WMA'], label=NAME5, color='tab:gray')
    a_x.plot(x_1, sym1_hist['SSF'], label=NAME17, color='tab:red')
    a_x.plot(x_1, sym1_hist['alpha_beta'], label=NAME19, color='tab:purple')

    # have a plot title:
    plt.title(NAME1, fontsize=18, y = 1.05)
    plt.suptitle(suptitle, fontsize=14, y = 0.912)

    a_x.legend(fontsize=14)

    # rotate x-axis text:
    plt.xticks(rotation=45, fontsize=14)
    plt.yticks(fontsize=14)

    # turn a grid on:
    plt.grid()

    # save plot:
    fig.savefig(FILENAME)

    # plt.show()
#
############################################################



############################################################
#
# send an email alert with attachment:
def send_email_attach(chart_file_name, message_str):
    """
    send a text message plus hardcopy attachment from
    one Yahoo email account to another Yahoo email account
    via a unique app pw for smtplib
    """
    from_me = '<name1>@<domain>'
    to_you = '<name2>@<domain>'


    print(chart_file_name)  # use only later

    subj = 'Email alert from tsla_alerts_on_chart_signals.py'
    date = formatdate(localtime=True)
    # see:
    # https://stackoverflow.com/questions/3362600/how-to-send-email-attachments

    # msg = "From: %s\nTo: %s\nSubject: %s\nDate: %s\n\n%s" %\
    # (from_me, to_you, subj, date, message_str)
    # --> better as a f-string:
    msg = f"From: {from_me}\nTo: {to_you}\nSubject: {subj}\nDate: {date}\n\n{message_str}"

    username = str('<name>')
    password = str('<pw>')

    try:
        server = smtplib.SMTP("smtp.mail.yahoo.com", 587)
        server.starttls()
        server.login(username,password)
        server.sendmail(from_me, to_you, msg)
        server.quit()
        print("OK, the email has been sent")

    except Exception as error:
        print("Cannot send the email: ", error)

#
############################################################


############################################################
# main program body:
#

# initialize flags:
sym1_hist = sym1.history(period=DAYS_STR)  # yfinance: new version on 2023-04-09!!

prices = sym1_hist['Open'].values  # this is only a "shallow copy"!!
sym1_hist['alpha_beta'] = a_b_filter(data=prices)
sym1_hist['WMA'] = ta.wma(sym1_hist['Open'], length=MA2)
ssf_raw = ta.ssf(sym1_hist['Open'], length=MA4, poles=SSF_POLES)
# suppress output prior to full length of input:
empt = np.empty(MA4)
empt[:] = np.nan
ssf_temp = ssf_raw
ssf_temp[:MA4] = empt
sym1_hist['SSF'] = ssf_temp

# ini change on 2023-05-09 @ 07:21 PM:
if long_crossover(sym1_hist['Open'], sym1_hist['WMA']) and\
    long_crossover(sym1_hist['Open'], sym1_hist['SSF']) and\
        long_crossover(sym1_hist['Open'], sym1_hist['alpha_beta']):
    SHORT_FLAG = 1  # 1 = waiting for first short signal
    LONG_FLAG = 0  # 0 = not waiting for more long signals

elif short_crossover(sym1_hist['Open'], sym1_hist['WMA']) and\
    short_crossover(sym1_hist['Open'], sym1_hist['SSF']) and\
        short_crossover(sym1_hist['Open'], sym1_hist['alpha_beta']):
    SHORT_FLAG = 0  # 0 = waiting for more short signals
    LONG_FLAG = 1  # 1 = waiting for first long signal

# the case of a sideways market: decide for one side: here short:
else:
    SHORT_FLAG = 1
    LONG_FLAG = 0

FIRST_EMAIL_ACTIVATION = 1
FLAG_CHANGE = 1

LONG_WMA = 0  # 0 = no long signal happened
LONG_SSF = 0
LONG_ALPHA_BETA = 0

SHORT_WMA = 0  # 0 = no short signal happened
SHORT_SSF = 0
SHORT_ALPHA_BETA = 0
#
# end of initialize flags


DAY = 0  # don't run program eternally
while DAY < 760:  # 3 years = 3 * 252 = ~760

    # check time: is it after 1200h local time?
    # --> if yes run this part, otherwise wait another 60 Minutes
    TRIGGER_TIME_STR = '18:00:00'  # use U.S. lunch time, not German time
    trigger_obj = datetime.datetime.strptime(TRIGGER_TIME_STR, '%H:%M:%S')
    # prevent 2 or 3 emails within 1 hour:
    trigger_limit = trigger_obj + datetime.timedelta(hours=0, minutes=59, seconds=59)
    trigger_limit_time = trigger_limit.time()
    trigger_obj_time = trigger_obj.time()
    ct = datetime.datetime.now()

    # weekday check:
    # ct.isoweekday(): 1 = Mon, 6 = Fri
    #
    # only go here if time diff < 1h
    # --> what happens if started > 1900h German time? --> wait till next day!
    if ct.isoweekday() < 6 and trigger_obj_time <= ct.time() < trigger_limit_time:
    # 2023-05-13

        # fetch quotes:
        sym1_hist = sym1.history(period=DAYS_STR)  # yfinance: new version on 2023-04-09!!
        # signaling at open --> trading at close of same day:
        prices = sym1_hist['Open'].values  # this is only a "shallow copy"!!

        # check: are quotes of the day there?
        # - today could be a holiday
        # - there could be no new quotes from Yahoo Finance
        DAY_OK = sym1_hist.index[-1].date() == datetime.datetime.today().date()

        if DAY_OK:
            ts = round(ct.timestamp())
            FILENAME = 'tsla_alerts_on_chart_signals, ' + str(ts) + '.png'

            ######
            #
            # make filter data:
            sym1_hist['alpha_beta'] = a_b_filter(data=prices)

            sym1_hist['WMA'] = ta.wma(sym1_hist['Open'], length=MA2)

            ssf_raw = ta.ssf(sym1_hist['Open'], length=MA4, poles=SSF_POLES)
            # suppress output prior to full length of input:
            empt = np.empty(MA4)
            empt[:] = np.nan
            ssf_temp = ssf_raw
            ssf_temp[:MA4] = empt
            sym1_hist['SSF'] = ssf_temp
            #
            ######

            if LONG_FLAG == 1:  # 1 = waiting for first long signal
                if long_crossover(sym1_hist['Open'], sym1_hist['WMA']):
                    if LONG_WMA == 0:
                        FLAG_CHANGE = 1
                    LONG_WMA = 1
                if long_crossover(sym1_hist['Open'], sym1_hist['SSF']):
                    if LONG_SSF == 0:
                        FLAG_CHANGE = 1
                    LONG_SSF = 1
                if long_crossover(sym1_hist['Open'], sym1_hist['alpha_beta']):
                    if LONG_ALPHA_BETA == 0:
                        FLAG_CHANGE = 1
                    LONG_ALPHA_BETA = 1

                FULL_HOUSE = LONG_WMA == 1 and LONG_SSF == 1 and LONG_ALPHA_BETA == 1

                if FIRST_EMAIL_ACTIVATION == 1 and FLAG_CHANGE == 1:  # 2023-05-19
                    hardcopy()
                    send_email_attach(FILENAME, "Long $TSLA at Close!")
                    FIRST_EMAIL_ACTIVATION = 0

                if FULL_HOUSE:
                    hardcopy()
                    send_email_attach(FILENAME, "Waiting for first short signal.")
                    LONG_FLAG = 0
                    SHORT_FLAG = 1
                    LONG_WMA = 0
                    LONG_SSF = 0
                    LONG_ALPHA_BETA = 0
                    FIRST_EMAIL_ACTIVATION = 1
                    FLAG_CHANGE = 1

                # check for false long market and go short if needed:
                else:
                    if short_crossover(sym1_hist['Open'], sym1_hist['WMA']):
                        if LONG_WMA == 1:
                            FLAG_CHANGE = 1
                        LONG_WMA = 0
                    if short_crossover(sym1_hist['Open'], sym1_hist['SSF']):
                        if LONG_SSF == 1:
                            FLAG_CHANGE = 1
                        LONG_SSF = 0
                    if short_crossover(sym1_hist['Open'], sym1_hist['alpha_beta']):
                        if LONG_ALPHA_BETA == 1:
                            FLAG_CHANGE = 1
                        LONG_ALPHA_BETA = 0

                    # 2023-05-19:
                    if LONG_WMA == 0 and LONG_SSF == 0 and LONG_ALPHA_BETA == 0 and\
                        FLAG_CHANGE == 1:
                        hardcopy()
                        send_email_attach(FILENAME,\
'Leaving a sideways market.\nShort $TSLA at Close!\nWaiting for first long signal.')
                        FIRST_EMAIL_ACTIVATION = 1


            elif SHORT_FLAG == 1:  # 1 = waiting for first short signal
                if short_crossover(sym1_hist['Open'], sym1_hist['WMA']):
                    if SHORT_WMA == 0:
                        FLAG_CHANGE = 1
                    SHORT_WMA = 1
                if short_crossover(sym1_hist['Open'], sym1_hist['SSF']):
                    if SHORT_SSF == 0:
                        FLAG_CHANGE = 1
                    SHORT_SSF = 1
                if short_crossover(sym1_hist['Open'], sym1_hist['alpha_beta']):
                    if SHORT_ALPHA_BETA == 0:
                        FLAG_CHANGE = 1
                    SHORT_ALPHA_BETA = 1

                FULL_HOUSE = SHORT_WMA == 1 and SHORT_SSF == 1 and SHORT_ALPHA_BETA == 1

                if FIRST_EMAIL_ACTIVATION == 1 and FLAG_CHANGE == 1:  # 2023-05-19
                    hardcopy()
                    send_email_attach(FILENAME, "Short $TSLA at Close!")
                    FIRST_EMAIL_ACTIVATION = 0

                if FULL_HOUSE:
                    hardcopy()
                    send_email_attach(FILENAME, "Waiting for first long signal.")
                    LONG_FLAG = 1
                    SHORT_FLAG = 0
                    SHORT_WMA = 0
                    SHORT_SSF = 0
                    SHORT_ALPHA_BETA = 0
                    FIRST_EMAIL_ACTIVATION = 1
                    FLAG_CHANGE = 1

                # check for false short market and go long if needed:
                else:
                    if long_crossover(sym1_hist['Open'], sym1_hist['WMA']):
                        if SHORT_WMA == 1:
                            FLAG_CHANGE = 1
                        SHORT_WMA = 0
                    if long_crossover(sym1_hist['Open'], sym1_hist['SSF']):
                        if SHORT_SSF == 1:
                            FLAG_CHANGE = 1
                        SHORT_SSF = 0
                    if long_crossover(sym1_hist['Open'], sym1_hist['alpha_beta']):
                        if SHORT_ALPHA_BETA == 1:
                            FLAG_CHANGE = 1
                        SHORT_ALPHA_BETA = 0

                    # 2023-05-19:
                    if SHORT_WMA == 0 and SHORT_SSF == 0 and SHORT_ALPHA_BETA == 0 and\
                        FLAG_CHANGE == 1:
                        hardcopy()
                        send_email_attach(FILENAME,\
'Leaving a sideways market.\nLong $TSLA at Close!\nWaiting for first short signal.')
                        FIRST_EMAIL_ACTIVATION = 1


            # save flags here for supervision:
            # - only do this in flag changeover situations
            # - build one text string to bring all data together
            if FLAG_CHANGE == 1:
                FLAG_STR = "\n  SHORT_FLAG = " + str(SHORT_FLAG) +\
                      "\n  LONG_FLAG = " + str(LONG_FLAG) +\
                      "\n  FIRST_EMAIL_ACTIVATION  = " + str(FIRST_EMAIL_ACTIVATION) +\
                      "\n  LONG_WMA = " + str(LONG_WMA) +\
                      "\n  LONG_SSF = " + str(LONG_SSF) +\
                      "\n  LONG_ALPHA_BETA= " + str(LONG_ALPHA_BETA) +\
                      "\n  SHORT_WMA = " + str(SHORT_WMA) +\
                      "\n  SHORT_SSF = " + str(SHORT_SSF) +\
                      "\n  SHORT_ALPHA_BETA = " + str(SHORT_ALPHA_BETA)

                LINE = "\n" + str(ct) + "\tflags:" + FLAG_STR
                # write to disk: append file MEAS_DATA_FILE
                #
                with open(DATA_FILE, "a", encoding="utf-8") as file:
                    file.write(LINE)
                    file.close()

                FLAG_CHANGE = 0

            DAY += 1


    # sleep for 1 hour:
    # - this program should start OK after (almost) every manual start at a server!
    time.sleep(3600)
    # time.sleep(3)


# end of main program body
#
############################################################


# end of tsla_alerts_on_chart_signals.py

title: On Time for the Exam
content:
start_exam_hour = int(input())
start_exam_minutes = int(input())
hour_of_arrive = int(input())
minute_of_arrive = int(input())
diff_minutes = 0
hour = 0
minutes = 0

exam_time_in_minutes = (start_exam_hour * 60) + start_exam_minutes
exam_time_of_arrive_in_minutes = (hour_of_arrive * 60) + minute_of_arrive

if exam_time_of_arrive_in_minutes == exam_time_in_minutes:
    print('On time')

elif exam_time_of_arrive_in_minutes < exam_time_in_minutes:
    diff_minutes = exam_time_in_minutes - exam_time_of_arrive_in_minutes
    hour = diff_minutes // 60
    minutes = diff_minutes % 60

    if diff_minutes <= 30:
        print('On time')
        print(f'{minutes} minutes before the start')
    else:
        print('Early')
        if diff_minutes < 60:
            print(f'{minutes} minutes before the start')
        else:
            print(f'{hour}:{minutes:02d} hours before the start')

elif exam_time_of_arrive_in_minutes > exam_time_in_minutes:
    diff_minutes = exam_time_of_arrive_in_minutes - exam_time_in_minutes
    hour = diff_minutes // 60
    minutes = diff_minutes % 60
    print('Late')
    if diff_minutes < 60:
        print(f'{diff_minutes} minutes after the start')
    else:
        print(f'{hour}:{minutes:02d} hours after the start')

    end
end

content:
#-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Item Find
# v2.0
# By Boonzeet
#-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# A script to show a helpful message with item name, icon and description
# when an item is found for the first time.
#-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

WINDOWSKIN_NAME = "" # set for custom windowskin

#-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Save data registry
#-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
SaveData.register(:item_log) do
  save_value { $item_log }
  load_value { |value|  $item_log = value }
  new_game_value { ItemLog.new }
end

#-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Base Class
#-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

class PokemonItemFind_Scene
  def pbStartScene
    @viewport = Viewport.new(0, 0, Graphics.width, Graphics.height)
    @viewport.z = 99999
    @sprites = {}
    skin = WINDOWSKIN_NAME == "" ? MessageConfig.pbGetSystemFrame : "Graphics/Windowskins/" + WINDOWSKIN_NAME
    
    
    @sprites["background"] = Window_UnformattedTextPokemon.newWithSize("", 0, 0, Graphics.width, 0, @viewport)
    @sprites["background"].z = @viewport.z - 1
    @sprites["background"].visible = false
    @sprites["background"].setSkin(skin)
    
    colors = getDefaultTextColors(@sprites["background"].windowskin)

    @sprites["itemicon"] = ItemIconSprite.new(42, Graphics.height - 48, nil, @viewport)
    @sprites["itemicon"].visible = false
    @sprites["itemicon"].z = @viewport.z + 2
	
    @sprites["descwindow"] = Window_UnformattedTextPokemon.newWithSize("", 64, 0, Graphics.width - 64, 64, @viewport)
    @sprites["descwindow"].windowskin = nil
    @sprites["descwindow"].z = @viewport.z
    @sprites["descwindow"].visible = false
    @sprites["descwindow"].baseColor = colors[0]
    @sprites["descwindow"].shadowColor = colors[1]

    @sprites["titlewindow"] = Window_UnformattedTextPokemon.newWithSize("", 0, 0, 128, 16, @viewport)
    @sprites["titlewindow"].visible = false
    @sprites["titlewindow"].z = @viewport.z + 1
    @sprites["titlewindow"].windowskin = nil
    @sprites["titlewindow"].baseColor = colors[0]
    @sprites["titlewindow"].shadowColor = colors[1]
  end

  def pbShow(item)
    item_object = GameData::Item.get(item)
    name = item_object.name
    description = item_object.description

    descwindow = @sprites["descwindow"]
    descwindow.resizeToFit(description, Graphics.width - 64)
    descwindow.text = description
    descwindow.y = Graphics.height - descwindow.height
    descwindow.visible = true

    titlewindow = @sprites["titlewindow"]
    titlewindow.resizeToFit(name, Graphics.height)
    titlewindow.text = name
    titlewindow.y = Graphics.height - descwindow.height - 32
    titlewindow.visible = true

    background = @sprites["background"]
    background.height = descwindow.height + 32
    background.y = Graphics.height - background.height
    background.visible = true

    itemicon = @sprites["itemicon"]
    itemicon.item = item
    itemicon.y = Graphics.height - (descwindow.height / 2).floor
    itemicon.visible = true

    loop do
      background.update
      itemicon.update
      descwindow.update
      titlewindow.update
      Graphics.update
      Input.update
      pbUpdateSceneMap
      if Input.trigger?(Input::B) || Input.trigger?(Input::C)
        pbEndScene
        break
      end
    end
  end

  def pbEndScene
    pbDisposeSpriteHash(@sprites)
    @viewport.dispose
  end
end


#-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Item Log class
#-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# The store of found items
#-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
class ItemLog
  def initialize()
    @found_items = []
  end

  def register(item)
    if !@found_items.include?(item)
      @found_items.push(item)
      scene = PokemonItemFind_Scene.new
      scene.pbStartScene
      scene.pbShow(item)
    end
  end
end

#-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Overrides of pbItemBall and pbReceiveItem
#-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Picking up an item found on the ground
#-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

alias pbItemBall_itemfind pbItemBall
def pbItemBall(item,quantity=1)
  result = pbItemBall_itemfind(item,quantity)
  $item_log.register(item) if result
  return result
end

alias pbReceiveItem_itemfind pbReceiveItem
def pbReceiveItem(item,quantity=1)
  result = pbReceiveItem_itemfind(item,quantity)
  $item_log.register(item) if result
  return result
end

alias pbPickBerry_itemfind pbPickBerry
def pbPickBerry(berry, qty = 1)
  pbPickBerry_itemfind(berry,qty)
  $item_log.register(berry) if $PokemonBag.pbHasItem?(berry)
end

<?php

/**
 * PHP version 7.0
 *
 * Class WC_Retailcrm_Order_Item - Build items for CRM order.
 *
 * @category Integration
 * @author   RetailCRM <integration@retailcrm.ru>
 * @license  http://retailcrm.ru Proprietary
 * @link     http://retailcrm.ru
 * @see      http://help.retailcrm.ru
 */
class WC_Retailcrm_Order_Item extends WC_Retailcrm_Abstracts_Data
{
    /**
     * @var array order item
     */
    protected $data = [
        'offer' => [],
        'productName' => '',
        'initialPrice' => 0.00,
        'quantity' => 0.00
    ];

    /**
     * @var array
     */
    protected $settings = [];

    /**
     * WC_Retailcrm_Order_Item constructor.
     *
     * @param array $settings
     */
    public function __construct($settings)
    {
        $this->settings = $settings;
    }

    /**
     * @param WC_Order_Item_Product $item
     *
     * @return self
     */
    public function build($item)
    {
        $decimalPlaces = wc_get_price_decimals();

        // Calculate price and discount
        $price         = $this->calculatePrice($item, $decimalPlaces);
        $discountPrice = $this->calculateDiscount($item, $price, $decimalPlaces);

        $data['productName']  = $item['name'];
        $data['initialPrice'] = $price;
        $data['quantity']     = (double)$item['qty'];

        $itemId = ($item['variation_id'] > 0) ? $item['variation_id'] : $item['product_id'];
        $data['externalIds'] = [
            [
                'code' => 'woocomerce',
                'value' => $itemId . '_' . $item->get_id(),
            ]
        ];

        # start custom #
        $sale_price = false;
        if($item['variation_id'] > 0) {
            $price_obj = get_variation_price_by_id($item['product_id'], $item['variation_id']);
            $sale_price = $price_obj->display_price !== false ? true : false;
        }
        //$sale_price = get_post_meta( $item['product_id'], '_sale_price', true) && get_post_meta( $item['product_id'], '_sale_price', true); > 0 ? true : false;

        $price_type = array(
            'code' => $sale_price ? 'sale-price' : 'retail-price'
        );

        $data['priceType'] = $price_type;

        # end custom #

        $this->setDataFields($data);
        $this->setOffer($item);
        $this->setField('discountManualAmount', $discountPrice);

        return $this;
    }

    /**
     * @param WC_Order_Item_Product $item
     *
     * @return void
     */
    private function setOffer(WC_Order_Item_Product $item)
    {
        $uid   = $item['variation_id'] > 0 ? $item['variation_id'] : $item['product_id'] ;
        $offer = ['externalId' => $uid];

        $product = $item->get_product();

        if (
            !empty($product)
            && isset($this->settings['bind_by_sku'])
            && $this->settings['bind_by_sku'] == WC_Retailcrm_Base::YES
        ) {
            $offer['xmlId'] = $product->get_sku();
            # TEMPORARY COMMENT THIS UNSET SECTION 
            //unset($offer['externalId']);
        }

        $this->setField('offer', $offer);
    }

    /**
     * @param WC_Order_Item_Product $item
     * @param int $decimalPlaces Price rounding from WC settings
     *
     * @return float
     */
    private function calculatePrice(WC_Order_Item_Product $item, int $decimalPlaces)
    {
        $price = ($item['line_subtotal'] / $item->get_quantity()) + ($item['line_subtotal_tax'] / $item->get_quantity());

        return round($price, $decimalPlaces);
    }

    /**
     * @param WC_Order_Item_Product $item
     * @param $price
     * @param int $decimalPlaces Price rounding from WC settings
     *
     * @return float|int
     */
    private function calculateDiscount(WC_Order_Item_Product $item, $price, int $decimalPlaces)
    {
        $productPrice  = $item->get_total() ? $item->get_total() / $item->get_quantity() : 0;
        $productTax    = $item->get_total_tax() ? $item->get_total_tax() / $item->get_quantity() : 0;
        $itemPrice     = $productPrice + $productTax;

        return round($price - $itemPrice, $decimalPlaces);
    }

    /**
     * Reset item data.
     */
    public function resetData()
    {
        $this->data = [
            'offer' => [],
            'productName' => '',
            'initialPrice' => 0.00,
            'quantity' => 0.00
        ];
    }
}
